            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing B. F. Foster.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Nashville</placeName>, <date when="1826-11-05">November 5. 1826</date></p>
<p>Sir:</p>

<p>Altho not personally known to you, I make no apology for 
introducing to your acquaintance<persName> Colo Benjamin F Foster</persName> of this place,
who goes to <placeName>Texas </placeName>as the <persName>agent </persName>for the <placeName><persName>Leftwich</persName> Grant.</placeName></p>

<p><persName>Colo Foster</persName> is a young <persName>Lawyer </persName>of fine education and good talents&#8212;
of extensive and highly respectable connections and has always 
sustained the character of a moral, intelligent and honorable young
<persName>gentleman</persName>-&#8212;As such it gives me pleasure to recommend him to your
kind civilities and friendly offices.</p>

<p><persName>Wm. Carroll</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Colo. Stephen F Austin</persName> <placeName>Texas</placeName>.    <persName>Colo Foster</persName>.</p>



        </div1>
